fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
Pullbacks, hence kernel pairs, exist and their coequalizers are quotient
  groups. It remains to show that regular epis are stable
  under pullback. Since epis are surjections and every
  surjection is the coequalizer of its kernel pair, it in particular remains to show that
  surjections are stable under pullback. Consider a diagram 




